rincipality time, around 1000 1016. He ruled protracted war Byzantine Empire First Bulgarian Empire. His close relationship Byzantium save Duklja expansionist Tsar Samuel Bulgaria, conquered principality around 1010 took Jovan Vladimir prisoner. A medieval chronicle asserts Samuel's daughter, Theodora Kosara, fell love Vladimir begged father hand. The tsar allowed marriage returned Duklja Vladimir, ruled vassal. Vladimir acknowledged pious, just, peaceful ruler. He took part father-in-law's war efforts. The warfare culminated Samuel's defeat Byzantines 1014; tsar died soon afterward. In 1016 Vladimir fell victim plot Ivan Vladislav, last ruler First Bulgarian Empire. He beheaded front church Prespa, empire's capital, buried there. He soon recognized martyr saint; feast day celebrated 22 May. His widow, Kosara, reburied Prečista Krajinska Church, near court southeastern Duklja. In 1381 remains preserved Church Saint Jovan Vladimir near Elbasan, since 1995 kept Orthodox cathedral Tirana, Albania. The saint's remains considered relics, attract many believers, especially feast day, relics taken church near Elbasan celebration. ...Archive/Nominations Read more... edit Did know... ... Giovanni de Ventura, plague doctor may worn beak doctor costume (pictured), restricted covenant treat infectious patients? In nose mask, types plants used filter sickness wearer. ... archaic Greek alphabets, Ε could look like Β, Β like C, Γ like Ι, Ι like Σ, Σ like Μ? ... Chinese government published list sixty-four important cultural relics forbidden exhibited outside China? ... 1886 novel Albertine expedited abolition public prostitution Norway? ... Carl Sagan worked US Air Force detonating nuclear device Moon? ... Olympic gold medals made silver, jade, glass? ... 1945 Japanese battalion rearmed serve alongside British 5th Parachute Brigade Far East? ... Solomon accidentally castrated infant? ...Archive/Nominations More... edit Selected picture Buzz Aldrin's footprint, taken Apollo 11, fir